{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"layoutPriority"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"value"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"value","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The priority by which a parent layout apportions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space to the child."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views typically have a default priority of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":" which causes space to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"apportioned evenly to all sibling views. Raising a view’s layout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"priority encourages the higher priority view to shrink later when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group is shrunk and stretch sooner when the group is stretched."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Text(\"This is a moderately long string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .border(Color.gray)","","    Spacer()","","    Text(\"This is a higher priority string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .layoutPriority(1)","        .border(Color.gray)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, the first "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" element has the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"priority "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which causes its view to shrink dramatically due to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"higher priority of the second "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" element, even though all of their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other attributes (font, font size and character count) are the same."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A parent layout offers the child views with the highest layout priority"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all the space offered to the parent minus the minimum space required for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all its lower-priority children."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/vstack\/layoutpriority(_:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack"]]},"metadata":{"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/LayoutPriority.swift#L49","fileName":"LayoutPriority.swift"},"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS",